# Render.com — Environment variables (copy names into Dashboard → Environment)
#
# FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON
#   Paste the FULL contents of your Firebase service account JSON file
#   (Project settings → Service accounts → Generate new private key).
#   Must be the SAME project as the mobile app (e.g. volvoegyptapp).
#
#   Render works best with ONE LINE (minified JSON). Example to minify locally:
#     python -c "import json,sys; print(json.dumps(json.load(open('your-key.json')), separators=(',',':')))"
#
#   Then paste the single line as the value of FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON.
#
# Optional alternative: upload the JSON file on the server and set
#   FIREBASE_CREDENTIALS_PATH=/path/to/volvoegyptapp-firebase-adminsdk-....json
